<p>Substitute values to $x$ approaching 0 from both sides.</p>

<figure style="text-align: center;">
  <img src="/images/content/DC/DC-2.5.3.png" alt="my alt text" width="400px" />
  <figcaption><em>
</em></figcaption>
</figure>

<p>The left and right hand limits <strong>both approaches to infinity</strong> as $x$ approaches 0. Hence,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
%	\lim_{x\to 0^-} &amp;= \lim_{x\to 0^+} \\  
	\lim_{x\to 0} &amp;= \infty		\tagans
\end{align*}\]

